## Persona content note

Muse persona YAML files contain interpretive commentary on the cognitive moves
of great thinkers. Content describing a thinker's approach is drawn from
publicly available sources (books, interviews, lectures) and is presented as
interpretive framework, not quotation.

For living figures or estate-protected names, persona files include explicit
disclaimers: "Interpretive frame based on public material. Not affiliated.
Not quotation."

Muse does not represent any living person or estate. Users invoking a persona
are interacting with a cognitive framework built by Muse contributors, not
with the person named.

If you are the estate of or represent a living figure included in Muse and
wish for the persona to be removed, please open an issue at the project
repository.
